t is not simply the history of individual departments scattered across the nation. Instead, the story reveals the many non-academic forces that made those departments possible, such as the creation of the United Church of Canada, the adoption of multiculturalism, and the introduction of the Charter of Rights and Freedoms. In recounting this transformation, From Seminary to University illuminates an important part of Canadian history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aReligionxStudy and teaching (Higher)zCanadaxHistory. 0aTheological seminarieszCanadaxHistory. 0aTheologyxStudy and teaching (Higher)zCanadaxHistory. 0aUniversities and collegesxCurriculazCanadaxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Post-Confederation (1867-).2bisacsh  aChristianity.  aMcGill.  aUniversity of Toronto.  achurch and state.  ahistory of religion.  areligion and politics.  areligious education.  areligious studies in Canada.  aseminary school.  asociology of knowledge.  atheology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP Pilot eBook-Package 2020z978311069045340uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753126340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487531263423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487531263.jpg  a978-3-11-069045-3  UTP Pilot eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishb2020  a